  "local_port": 41032,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am having problems with my friend. She is awesome, but she recently got a boyfriend. I just miss the way we once were. She's all over him and her other best friend. What should I do?",
  "response": "It\u2019s completely natural to feel this way when a close friend starts a new relationship, especially if it changes the dynamic between you. Here are some steps you can take to navigate this situation:\n\n### 1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**\n   - It\u2019s okay to feel left out or miss the way things were. Validate your emotions and understand that change can be hard, especially in relationships that mean a lot to you.\n\n### 2. **Communicate with Her**\n   - Have an honest but empathetic conversation with your friend. Let her know that you value your friendship and that you\u2019ve been feeling a bit left out. Avoid blaming or accusing her\u2014just share how you feel. For example:  \n     *\"I\u2019m so happy for you and your relationship, but I\u2019ve been missing the time we used to spend together. I just wanted to let you know how much our friendship means to me.\"*\n\n### 3. **Be Understanding**\n   - Remember that new relationships often come with a \u201choneymoon phase,\u201d where people are naturally more focused on their partner. This doesn\u2019t mean she values you any less\u2014it\u2019s just a temporary shift in priorities.\n\n### 4. **Make Plans Together**\n   - Suggest specific activities or times to hang out, just the two of you. Having dedicated time together can help you feel more connected and ensure your friendship remains strong.\n\n### 5. **Expand Your Circle**\n   - While it\u2019s important to nurture your friendship, it can also be helpful to focus on other relationships or hobbies. Spend time with other friends, join new activities, or explore interests that make you happy.\n\n### 6. **Give It Time**\n   - Relationships, including friendships, evolve over time. As things settle with her boyfriend, she may naturally find more balance between her relationships.\n\n### 7. **Be Patient and Supportive**\n   - Show interest in her life and her new relationship. Being supportive can strengthen your bond and remind her that you\u2019re there for her, no matter what.\n\n### 8. **Reflect on Your Own Needs**\n   - Take some time to think about what you need from your friendships and how you can communicate those needs in a healthy way. This can help you build stronger connections in all your relationships.\n\nRemember, friendships can adapt and grow, even when life changes. With open communication and mutual understanding, you can work through this and continue to have a meaningful connection with your friend.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
